credibility : 

Do not stop the site suddenly for maintenance, but specify the maintenance times + do not warn the user of any error that occurred in his request, whether it was rejected or at all, the request was not sent for an error


consistency : 

  That the pages of the site are consistent with each other and that the basic design does not differ from one page to another, or even, for example, the student’s page is different in terms of design from the admin page or the institution’s page


Ease of use : 

So that the sites do not need instructions so that the user can deal with it

customer experience : 

The presence of a feedback system in the system, such as a feedback system or a complaints box system, to improve the general user experience of the system or product

